dcterms:description: A generative model where the adjacency matrix is generated by a random dot product graph, which is used to study the performance of graph convolutional networks and adjacency spectral embedding.
dcterms:title: Random Dot Product Graph (RDPG)

dcterms:description: A model for representing the structure of a network where nodes are grouped into communities, with varying probabilities of connections between groups.
dcterms:title: Stochastic Block Model

dcterms:creator: P. Rubin-Delanchy
C. E. Priebe
M. Tang
dcterms:description: An extension of the stochastic block model that allows for nodes to belong to multiple communities with varying membership probabilities.
dcterms:title: Mixed Membership Stochastic Block Model

dcterms:creator: Y. Zhao
E. Levina
J. Zhu
dcterms:description: A model that corrects for degree heterogeneity in networks, allowing for more accurate community detection.
dcterms:title: Degree-Corrected Stochastic Block Model
